You want session-based restriction like this:

If Admin is logged in → User login should not be allowed in another tab

If User is logged in → Admin login should not be allowed in another tab

Only one role session at a time

This is a role session check in Laravel.

Solution Concept

When login happens:

Save the role in session

Before login, check session role

If another role exists → block login

Example:

session('role') = admin
or
session('role') = user
1----->️⃣ Admin Login Controller
public function adminLogin(Request $request)
{
    // check if user already logged in
    if(session('role') == 'user'){
        return back()->with('error','User already logged in. Logout first.');
    }

    if(Auth::attempt(['email'=>$request->email,'password'=>$request->password,'role'=>'admin'])){
        
        session(['role'=>'admin']);

        return redirect('/admin/dashboard');
    }

    return back()->with('error','Invalid credentials');
}
2----->️⃣ User Login Controller
public function userLogin(Request $request)
{
    if(session('role') == 'admin'){
        return back()->with('error','Admin already logged in. Logout first.');
    }

    if(Auth::attempt(['email'=>$request->email,'password'=>$request->password,'role'=>'user'])){
        
        session(['role'=>'user']);

        return redirect('/dashboard');
    }

    return back()->with('error','Invalid credentials');
}
3----->️⃣ Logout (Important)
public function logout()
{
    Auth::logout();

    session()->forget('role');

    return redirect('/login');
}
Flow
Situation	Result
Admin logged in	User login blocked
User logged in	Admin login blocked
Logout	Both allowed
Example Message

If admin logged:

Admin already logged in. Please logout first.

If user logged:

User already logged in. Please logout first.
