 once I login the user and in multiple tabs, I login the user in one tab I logout the user. It will reflect to all the another at a sitting tabs.

Yes, this is normal Laravel session behavior 

When a user logs in, Laravel creates one session for the browser.
All tabs share the same session.

So the scenario works like this:

Scenario

1.----->User logs in → Tab 1

session_id = ABC123
user = logged in

2.-----> Open Tab 2 / Tab 3

All tabs use the same session

session_id = ABC123
user = logged in

3.----->Logout from Tab 1

Laravel runs:

Auth::logout();
session()->invalidate();
session()->regenerateToken();

Now the session becomes:

session_id = deleted
user = logged out

4.-----> When Tab 2 or Tab 3 refreshes

Laravel checks authentication:

Auth::check() → false

So it redirects to login page.

Example Logout Code (Recommended)

Use this in both Admin logout and User logout:

public function logout(Request $request)
{
    Auth::logout();

    $request->session()->invalidate();
    $request->session()->regenerateToken();

    return redirect('/login');
}
Result
Action	Result
User login in one tab	Logged in all tabs
User logout in one tab	All tabs logged out
Admin logout	All admin tabs logged out

This is correct and secure behavior used in real applications.

 Small improvement (company-level):

